news.headline: Wall Street plunges as Trump announces new tariffs: S&P 500 fell 1% to 6,045, Dow Jones down 0.8% to 44,530, Nasdaq 100 declined 1.5%. Bitcoin dropped 3%, Dollar soared.
news.summary: Updated information correctly attributes the tariff announcement to the Trump administration. U.S. equity indices saw a shift from gains to losses during Friday afternoon trading in New York. The White House confirmed new tariffs on imports from Canada, Mexico, and China, resulting in escalating trade tensions with these key suppliers. The S&P 500, as tracked by the SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (NYSE:SPY), fell by 1%, dropping from 6,120 points to 6,045 points by 2:45 p.m. ET. The Dow Jones Industrial Average also experienced a decline of 0.8% to 44,530 points, while the Nasdaq 100, monitored by the Invesco QQQ Trust, Series 1 (NASDAQ:QQQ), decreased by 1.5% after initially rising by 1.3%. In terms of sectors, the Energy Select Sector SPDR Fund (NYSE:XLE) plunged by 2.9%, while the Communication Services Select Sector SPDR Fund (NYSE: identifier not provided) also showed significant losses. For a more detailed account, please refer to the full story available on Benzinga.com.
